    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that Pakistan has ''outlined an ambitious campaign aimed at slowly curbing networks of militants that have taken root'' at home and in Afghanistan (news article, June 10). In its brief tenure, the government of Gen. Pervez Musharraf has shown neither the power nor the will to rein in the venomous influences of the Taliban or its own indigenous terrorist network.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that Pakistan has ''outlined an ambitious campaign aimed at slowly curbing networks of militants that have taken root'' at home and in Afghanistan (news article, June 10). In its brief tenure, the government of Gen. Pervez Musharraf has shown neither the power nor the will to rein in the venomous influences of the Taliban or its own indigenous terrorist network.</p>
        <p>Most recently, the junta backed down from a reform of the country's blasphemy law when the most powerful religious leaders threatened mass demonstrations. Any promises made by a military government, itself a sponsor and product of those fundamentalist training schools it intends to weaken, should be met in Washington with serious skepticism.</p>
        <p>CAMERON HUDSON  Washington, June 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
